title: Eric's Success Story
description: Eric's process was all about getting him out of his head, tongue tied, and floundering around what to say and transforming him into a man of solid confidence and masculinity so he could just be natural, have fun and flow while approaching and interacting with women.
caption: false

channel_info.title: Robbie Kramer
channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

transcription: {"text": "So before working with Interconfidence, I was really shy and just had a hard time talking to women. And even if I could, I didn't really know what to do with them. I felt like when I did hook up or fall in love, it was almost by accident. Now that I've been working with Interconfidence and taking their programs, I feel a lot more confident about approaching and talking to women. I feel like they respond a lot better to me and I'm just more comfortable in my own skin than I was before. I've recently started a relationship with this girl who unfortunately lives halfway across the country, but we started off being very kind of on a weird foot with each other, but since we've gotten to a very deep position where we trust each other well and talk a lot, and it's a very novel experience for me, I haven't really had that close a relationship with a woman before. I would say the one thing that I learned that got me from point A to point B would be learning to be more in my body, stop analyzing things as much, and I'm much more able to approach and talk to people of all life and just more confident with myself.
